            </div>
            <p className="text-sm text-slate-500 italic">Photo by RDNE Stock project from Pexels</p>
          </header>

          <div className="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p>Caring for someone with dementia requires understanding, patience, and specific skills. This comprehensive guide helps family caregivers understand dementia and provides effective communication strategies.</p>

            <h2>What is Dementia?</h2>
            <p>Dementia is not a specific disease but a general term for the impaired ability to remember, think, or make decisions that interferes with daily activities. The most common types include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Alzheimer's Disease (60-80% of cases)</li>
              <li>Vascular Dementia</li>
              <li>Lewy Body Dementia</li>
              <li>Frontotemporal Dementia</li>
              <li>Mixed Dementia</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Common Symptoms</h2>
            <p>Symptoms can vary but often include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Memory loss affecting daily activities</li>
              <li>Difficulty with planning and problem solving</li>
              <li>Confusion with time or place</li>
              <li>Problems with words in speaking or writing</li>
              <li>Changes in mood and personality</li>
              <li>Decreased judgment</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Effective Communication Strategies</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Maintain a calm and gentle tone</li>
              <li>Speak clearly and use simple sentences</li>
              <li>Allow time for responses</li>
              <li>Avoid arguing or correcting</li>
              <li>Use visual cues when possible</li>
              <li>Maintain eye contact</li>
              <li>Minimize distractions during conversations</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Daily Care Tips</h2>
            <p>Creating a supportive environment includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Establishing regular routines</li>
              <li>Simplifying tasks and instructions</li>
              <li>Ensuring a safe environment</li>
              <li>Encouraging independence when appropriate</li>
              <li>Providing meaningful activities</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Managing Behavioral Changes</h2>
            <p>Common behaviors and coping strategies:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Agitation: Identify triggers and maintain calm environment</li>
              <li>Wandering: Ensure safety measures and supervision</li>
              <li>Sundowning: Adjust activities and lighting</li>
              <li>Repetitive behavior: Use distraction and reassurance</li>
            </ul>

            <div className="bg-primary/5 p-6 rounded-xl mt-8">
              <h3>Self-Care for Caregivers</h3>
              <p>Remember to:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Take regular breaks</li>
                <li>Join support groups</li>
                <li>Accept help from others</li>
                <li>Maintain your own health</li>
                <li>Seek professional support when needed</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </main>
      <Footer />
    </>
  );
};

